-Depleted Tired Cookies:
-Base Ingredients
185 g all-purpose flour
25 g dark brown sugar
200 g granulated sugar
8 tbsp unsalted butter
-Flavor Ingredients
200 g chocolate
1.0 tsp soy sauce
---
Instructions
Step 1: Preheat the oven to 425 degrees F.
Step 2: Mix together dry ingredients, combining flour, , in a large bowl. In another bowl, cream together dark brown sugar, granulated sugar and unsalted butter, then add soy sauce.
Step 3: Gradually add the dry ingredients to the wet ingredients, mixing well. Once mixed, add the chocolate.
Step 4: Let the mixture rest for 10 hours in the refrigerator. On a baking sheet lined with parchment paper, add 40 grams of dough, rolled into a sphere. Bake for 11 minutes, turning the sheet around halfway through the baking time.
Step 5: Let the cookies cool.